        <mxCell id="rcU31Glp0nWZlW3K-Kab-13" parent="1" style="shape=process;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;backgroundOutline=1;fontFamily=Geist Mono;fontSource=https%3A%2F%2Ffonts.googleapis.com%2Fcss%3Ffamily%3DGeist%2BMono;sketch=1;curveFitting=1;jiggle=2;shadow=1;" value="Catalyst" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="40" width="160" x="130" y="20" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="tWjeZrfbFuTckyrvRVRW-1" parent="1" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=top;rounded=0;labelPosition=center;verticalLabelPosition=middle;fontFamily=Geist Mono;horizontal=1;fontSource=https%3A%2F%2Ffonts.googleapis.com%2Fcss%3Ffamily%3DGeist%2BMono;fontSize=12;sketch=1;curveFitting=1;jiggle=2;shadow=1;whiteSpace=wrap;" value="&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 150%;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;How it should work?&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;VirtEnforce runs as daemon with cli flag.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;During Startup, it audits the existing domains for reconciliation loop.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Subscribes to Libvirt Broadcast Events (Disk and VM lifecycle).&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Reacts to specfic DISKATTACH and VMSTART / VMRESUME events with&amp;nbsp;&lt;font&gt;VMIOPSEnforcement flow.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Subscribe to volume.QOS.subs subject. Catalyst will publish any QOS upgrade messages to this subject. Each hypervisor will read the message and execute this workflow&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;Check if the VM mentioned on the message exists in that node with libvirt and is in active state.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Step 1 is false -&amp;gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;Nothing to be done&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Acknowledge the message.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;Step 1 is true -&amp;gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;Runs&amp;nbsp;&lt;font&gt;VMIOPSEnforcement flow.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;font&gt;Writes a success/failure message to volume.QOS.notification (this will let catalyst know about the outcome.)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;font&gt;Acknowledge the message.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="470" width="410" x="380" y="250" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="4vxhtcBkbW7qOjsE2znI-1" parent="1" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=top;rounded=0;labelPosition=center;verticalLabelPosition=middle;fontFamily=Geist Mono;horizontal=1;fontSource=https%3A%2F%2Ffonts.googleapis.com%2Fcss%3Ffamily%3DGeist%2BMono;fontSize=12;sketch=1;curveFitting=1;jiggle=2;shadow=1;whiteSpace=wrap;" value="&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 150%;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;What it solves?&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Eliminates the need for frequent audits. 10 mins -&amp;gt; 3/6 hours&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Instant updates to the volume, rather than a wait period.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Reduces load on Openstack API Servers.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;What complexities it adds?&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;NATS with Jetstream needs to be deployed on Controllers. HA Setup with 3 replicas and 10GB persistent local volume disk.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Catalyst needs to integrate with NATS (I think this is new)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Although NATS is simple to setup and heals well during node failures, it&#39;s another component to manage.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="280" width="490" x="-80" y="580" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="4vxhtcBkbW7qOjsE2znI-3" parent="1" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=top;rounded=0;labelPosition=center;verticalLabelPosition=middle;fontFamily=Geist Mono;horizontal=1;fontSource=https%3A%2F%2Ffonts.googleapis.com%2Fcss%3Ffamily%3DGeist%2BMono;fontSize=12;sketch=1;curveFitting=1;jiggle=2;shadow=1;whiteSpace=wrap;" value="&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;Why not a REST API?&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li style=&quot;line-height: 150%;&quot;&gt;Hypervisor side car agents run locally one each node, and does not know about each other.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li style=&quot;line-height: 150%;&quot;&gt;Exposing each of these via REST needs authz/authn on each of these nodes, and since each of them are independent, it&#39;s an operational nightmare to have something like sqlite to store user data. OIDC is an option, but currently this increases the complexities on the app side.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li style=&quot;line-height: 150%;&quot;&gt;We are trying to keep the application as stateless as possible.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li style=&quot;line-height: 150%;&quot;&gt;What happens when virt-enforce is not running for a while, catalyst gets a 500 when it sends POST /qos/update/UUID.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="280" width="470" x="-580" y="330" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
      </root>
    </mxGraphModel>
  </diagram>
</mxfile>
